22:24.377 --> 22:26.277
Something between
[bleep] and awful.

22:26.312 --> 22:28.079
What does it mean

22:28.114 --> 22:29.914
when it feels like an elephant's
sitting on your chest?

22:29.949 --> 22:31.816
Oh, you don't have a heart.
You can't have a heart attack.

22:31.851 --> 22:33.384
(Jonathan)
Are you hungry, Gordon?

22:33.419 --> 22:34.952
What is this?

22:37.757 --> 22:40.057
That is bacon.
Should be on a different shelf.

22:40.093 --> 22:41.392
And this here?

22:41.427 --> 22:44.362
That shouldn't
be thrown there either.

22:45.932 --> 22:47.198
What's that?

22:47.233 --> 22:48.766
Beer batter
for the beer-battered shrimp.

22:48.801 --> 22:51.135
That should be thrown out.

22:51.170 --> 22:53.037
And this one?
Let me just set that on top.

22:53.072 --> 22:54.305
Sure, put it right on top.

22:54.340 --> 22:56.173
What is all this?

22:59.011 --> 23:01.379
That was...

23:01.414 --> 23:02.480
bacon.

23:02.515 --> 23:04.415
- No, no, no.
- Okay.

23:04.450 --> 23:05.850
Why is it in the fridge
like this?

23:05.885 --> 23:08.052
I dropped it one shelf below.

23:08.087 --> 23:10.254
Instead of putting it where it
belongs, I put it on the corner.

23:10.289 --> 23:12.056
Normally these things
are pretty orderly.

23:12.091 --> 23:15.292
This is a complete
cluster[bleep].

23:15.328 --> 23:16.460
And what's that?

23:16.496 --> 23:18.796
Corned beef.

23:18.831 --> 23:20.297
Let's get outside.

23:20.333 --> 23:22.500
Lisa, let's go outside.

23:22.535 --> 23:24.135
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

23:24.170 --> 23:25.836
<i>(Gordon)</i>
<i>What is going on?</i>

23:25.872 --> 23:28.272
The whole operation is screwed.

23:28.307 --> 23:31.876
The kitchen, shocking.
The line, disaster.

23:31.911 --> 23:34.578
Cross-contaminated,
raw meat, cooked meat--

23:34.614 --> 23:36.280
[bleep] everywhere.

23:36.315 --> 23:38.416
And then the biggest asset
where all the money is

23:38.451 --> 23:40.584
is downstairs
in the wine cellar.

23:40.620 --> 23:43.154
Who's maintaining
standards here?

23:43.189 --> 23:44.755
He is.

23:44.791 --> 23:47.224
I cannot believe
what you've just done in there.

23:47.260 --> 23:49.026
I really enjoy it.

23:49.061 --> 23:51.262
- You can't enjoy that.
- I swear to God, I do.

23:51.297 --> 23:52.997
I must be, like, cuckoo
in the head or something.

23:53.032 --> 23:54.098
Well, you need help.

23:54.133 --> 23:56.133
- Maybe.
- He does.

23:56.169 --> 23:57.835
You need to wake up.

24:01.040 --> 24:02.840
[bleep].

24:06.212 --> 24:08.345
I think we can do this.
I know we can do this.

24:08.381 --> 24:10.981
Yeah, but not
just you and you.

24:11.017 --> 24:12.450
I want it to be you and I,

24:12.485 --> 24:15.052
because you so don't listen
to me most of the time.

24:15.087 --> 24:17.421
Like, when I tell you, "It's
time to come home, Jonathan.

24:17.457 --> 24:19.223
It's time to [bleep]
come to bed."

24:19.258 --> 24:21.091
And you just say,
"[bleep] you."

24:21.127 --> 24:24.595
You know, [bleep] you now.
[bleep] you, Jonathan.

24:24.630 --> 24:27.164
[crying]
I love you so much,
and you're such a great guy,

24:27.200 --> 24:29.166
but you suck
as a business partner.

24:29.202 --> 24:31.402
- You really suck.
- Thanks.

24:31.437 --> 24:33.437
So you want to re-create this.
You want to--

24:33.473 --> 24:35.306
Get divorced.

24:35.341 --> 24:37.107
I don't want to get divorced.
You want to get divorced?

24:37.143 --> 24:38.442
No, I don't want
to get divorced.

24:38.478 --> 24:40.411
Why has it always been
your way?

24:40.446 --> 24:42.413
'Cause you know more than me?

24:42.448 --> 24:44.048
Apparently I don't.

24:44.083 --> 24:47.117
I'm as stupid as you think I am,
if not worse.

24:47.153 --> 24:48.819
(Lisa)
[sighs] Thank God.

24:48.855 --> 24:50.554
Let's go in the back door.

24:50.590 --> 24:53.324
(Jonathan)
[sighs] [bleep].

24:53.359 --> 24:54.992
Okay, give me a drink.

24:55.027 --> 24:57.294
I couldn't get this down
fast enough.

24:57.330 --> 25:00.331
That looks pretty good.
All right.

25:00.366 --> 25:02.500
[bottles clinking]

25:02.535 --> 25:06.937
- Have a nice night.
- [laughs]

25:06.973 --> 25:08.205
Ahh.

25:08.241 --> 25:10.074
(Melissa)
It's gonna be okay.

25:10.109 --> 25:12.209
Thanks for being
on the other side.

25:12.245 --> 25:13.611
Appreciate it.

25:15.047 --> 25:16.614
[coughs]
Oh, sorry.

25:16.649 --> 25:19.016
[coughing]

25:19.051 --> 25:20.885
That bourbon
was really strong.

25:20.920 --> 25:22.353
[coughing]

25:22.388 --> 25:25.122
Crap.

25:25.157 --> 25:26.390
Crying again?

25:26.425 --> 25:28.459
It's not really crying.

25:28.494 --> 25:31.128
- It's just releasing.
- Release it.

25:31.163 --> 25:33.030
Lisa, can I have you and him
together, please?

25:33.065 --> 25:34.365
Sure.

25:37.904 --> 25:39.570
I'm unconvinced,

25:39.605 --> 25:42.540
and I've never met a couple
so undeserving of my time.

25:42.575 --> 25:45.910
And I think you, Lisa--
you're just faking it.

25:45.945 --> 25:49.179
I'm just trying--trying to get
through the night tonight.

25:49.215 --> 25:50.981
No, you're acting.

25:51.017 --> 25:53.217
The crocodile tears are there.
Next minute's a laugh.

25:53.252 --> 25:55.019
It's self-preservation.

25:55.054 --> 25:57.354
And it's the only way for me
to get through the day.

25:57.390 --> 25:59.023
There's no heart.
There's no feeling.

25:59.058 --> 26:00.591
- There's a lot of heart
- No, there's not.

26:00.626 --> 26:02.593
I love what I do.

26:02.628 --> 26:04.995
And what do you love--
drinking with your friends?

26:05.031 --> 26:06.397
I don't do much drinking.

26:06.432 --> 26:09.466
I'm not the party girl.
He's the party boy.

26:09.502 --> 26:12.269
So there's no parties way on
after service downstairs

26:12.305 --> 26:14.438
in the basement
with the customers?

26:14.473 --> 26:16.674
Not in the past,
like, ten years.

26:16.709 --> 26:19.143
Jonathan,
you've lost interest.

26:19.178 --> 26:20.678
I'm a mess.

26:20.713 --> 26:23.380
(Lisa)
Yeah, you are.

26:23.416 --> 26:26.717
So the first thing I want you
both to do is to pack a bag.

26:26.752 --> 26:28.719
I want you to get out of here.

26:28.754 --> 26:30.187
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

26:30.222 --> 26:31.655
Start packing.

26:36.228 --> 26:39.663
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

26:39.699 --> 26:42.266
<i> (Gordon)</i>
<i>After sending Lisa and Jonathan</i>
<i> away for the night,</i>

26:42.301 --> 26:44.234
<i> I'm hoping</i>
<i> they can start to realize</i>

26:44.270 --> 26:46.437
<i> the effects they are having</i>
<i> on the Vienna.</i>

26:46.472 --> 26:49.306
<i> But before they return,</i>
<i> I called a staff meeting...</i>

26:49.342 --> 26:50.541
Morning.

26:50.576 --> 26:52.376
- Good morning.
- Morning.

26:52.411 --> 26:54.211
<i> (Gordon)</i>
<i> So I can get</i>
<i> a better understanding</i>

26:54.246 --> 26:58.482
<i> of the damage that</i>
<i>Lisa and Jonathan are doing.</i>

26:58.517 --> 27:00.250
I didn't get a chance
to meet you yesterday.

27:00.286 --> 27:02.386
I'm Jamie.
Do the housekeeping here.

27:02.421 --> 27:04.121
Okay, great.

27:04.156 --> 27:05.556
Let's get one thing right.
I'm here to help.

27:05.591 --> 27:07.124
Having done my research,

27:07.159 --> 27:09.727
I mean, the one
positive feedback I've had

27:09.762 --> 27:11.395
is about how good
the staff are,

27:11.430 --> 27:13.464
'cause I know, you know,
just how bad things are,

27:13.499 --> 27:15.332
and having witnessed
that service last night,

27:15.368 --> 27:16.634
I'm appalled.

27:16.669 --> 27:17.801
Is it always like that?

27:17.837 --> 27:19.036
- Yes.
- Yes.

27:19.071 --> 27:20.704
- Screaming?
- Yes.

27:20.740 --> 27:22.740
People can hear them
in the dining room.

27:22.775 --> 27:25.175
I've had tables
that have asked

27:25.211 --> 27:27.044
if everything was okay
in the kitchen.

27:27.079 --> 27:29.813
We can't be expected
to be professional all the time

27:29.849 --> 27:31.682
when they're not professional.

27:31.717 --> 27:34.284
After our shift,
they'll sit down with a table

27:34.320 --> 27:37.554
and expect us to wait on them,
hand them drinks till midnight.

27:37.590 --> 27:39.323
If we leave, they get upset.

27:39.358 --> 27:41.091
So guests stay here,
and they're drinking downstairs

27:41.127 --> 27:43.093
in front of those guests,
sometimes with the guests.

27:43.129 --> 27:46.497
See, there's no separation
between business and personal.

27:46.532 --> 27:48.599
(man)
When you're sitting here
entertaining your table,

27:48.634 --> 27:51.201
she'll find something wrong
that you're doing,

27:51.237 --> 27:52.603
and she'll come
and point it at you

27:52.638 --> 27:54.071
right in front of your table.

27:54.106 --> 27:55.639
(Jamie)
She's just rude.

27:55.675 --> 27:58.175
She texts me sometimes
really rude text messages like,

27:58.210 --> 28:00.310
"Oh, you forgot this,"
or, "You forgot that,"

28:00.346 --> 28:02.079
or, "Why didn't you do this?"

28:02.114 --> 28:04.248
- And, "Why wasn't this done?"
- It's crazy.

28:04.283 --> 28:05.649
(man)
Another problem
that we've really been having

28:05.685 --> 28:07.251
is we don't have
an actual payroll system.

28:07.286 --> 28:08.852
There's no payroll system?

28:08.888 --> 28:10.754
And then they'll say,
"Yeah, I'll get you one."

28:10.790 --> 28:13.090
- And you just never...
- Asking for your salary?

28:13.125 --> 28:14.625
Yeah, we have to ask
for our checks.

28:14.660 --> 28:16.260
"Yeah, I got--
I got 20 bucks right now.

28:16.295 --> 28:18.162
"That's all I got right now.

28:18.197 --> 28:19.530
Tomorrow morning I'll see you."

28:19.565 --> 28:22.132
They're drip-feeding
your salaries.

28:22.168 --> 28:23.600
My bank
does not take the checks.

28:23.636 --> 28:25.169
Neither does mine.

28:25.204 --> 28:26.503
When was the last time

28:26.539 --> 28:27.838
you had a staff meeting
and discussed this?

28:27.873 --> 28:29.573
(all)
Never.

28:29.608 --> 28:31.575
I'm sorry, but I want
to put an end to all this.

28:31.610 --> 28:33.043
Here's what we're gonna do.

28:33.079 --> 28:36.080
They're arriving
any minute now.

28:36.115 --> 28:38.182
And my message to them is,
if they're not prepared

28:38.217 --> 28:41.085
to bring in a level
of professionalism

28:41.120 --> 28:43.687
and understand those boundaries
need to be met on a daily basis,

28:43.723 --> 28:46.557
they're gonna lose the inn,
and they're gonna lose you.

28:46.592 --> 28:49.593
Let me go and get them.

28:49.628 --> 28:51.662
I let myself continue
to be abused.

28:51.697 --> 28:53.831
<i> They need to know</i>
<i> that it has to change.</i>

28:53.866 --> 28:57.434
And it can't just
be brushed off anymore.

28:57.470 --> 28:58.869
I had a chat
with the team.

28:58.904 --> 29:01.105
They're not
in a good place.

29:01.140 --> 29:02.473
And you've abused them.

29:02.508 --> 29:05.242
There are no boundaries.
They're your staff.

29:05.277 --> 29:08.412
And they need to be treated
a certain way.

29:08.447 --> 29:10.781
Let's go to Jamie first.

29:10.816 --> 29:12.616
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

29:12.651 --> 29:15.519
I'm really concerned about the
abusive texts that you send him.

29:15.554 --> 29:17.454
Why would you send him
abusive texts?

29:17.490 --> 29:19.389
You would send me a picture,
like, "Oh, you forgot this,"

29:19.425 --> 29:20.858
or, "You didn't do this right."

29:20.893 --> 29:22.860
You told me that you worked
at a lot of other places

29:22.895 --> 29:24.561
and you knew how to clean,

29:24.597 --> 29:26.430
and then the toilets
aren't cleaned and stuff.

29:26.465 --> 29:27.765
It's really important.

29:27.800 --> 29:29.666
But some of that stuff
doesn't work.

29:29.702 --> 29:31.368
So it's, like,
I'm sitting there scrubbing,

29:31.403 --> 29:32.669
and nothing's coming up,
and you'll be like,

29:32.705 --> 29:34.505
"Well, go do it again."

29:34.540 --> 29:37.841
And it's like,
I'm trying to do what I can.

29:37.877 --> 29:42.546
None of these talented
individuals get paid on time.

29:42.581 --> 29:46.383
I want to know why
they don't get paid on time.

29:46.418 --> 29:49.520
Because I don't have a payroll
system in place right now.

29:49.555 --> 29:52.289
Well, that's
a [bleep] disgrace.

29:52.324 --> 29:54.658
That is disgusting.

29:54.693 --> 29:56.460
And then you want them
waiting on you

29:56.495 --> 29:58.729
up until all hours
of the early morning

29:58.764 --> 30:00.798
while they tidy up
after your crap

30:00.833 --> 30:04.701
and then you can't even be
bothered to pay them on time.

30:04.737 --> 30:06.970
It's a...
it's a mess.

30:07.006 --> 30:10.440
No, you are a mess.

30:10.476 --> 30:12.342
(Lisa)
I need to say
something, though--

30:12.378 --> 30:14.978
that almost every single person
here, we've given them loans.

30:15.014 --> 30:16.513
You're lending them money
to buy uniforms

30:16.549 --> 30:18.315
to work
in your [bleep] business.

30:18.350 --> 30:19.917
- Right.
- That's absurd?

30:19.952 --> 30:21.685
- Why?
- Why?

30:21.720 --> 30:23.654
Absurd to pay for a uniform?

30:23.689 --> 30:25.956
The business should be
providing the uniform.

30:25.991 --> 30:27.558
Well, maybe
we need to do that.

30:27.593 --> 30:28.759
Yes, you do.

30:28.794 --> 30:30.627
I never thought about it
that way.

30:30.663 --> 30:32.729
- Whose business is this?
- [sighs]

30:32.765 --> 30:36.366
(Jonathan)
I've tried to create here
a place where people can come

30:36.402 --> 30:38.669
and...

30:38.704 --> 30:42.706
and relax and escape
from their stressful lives.

30:42.741 --> 30:44.808
"Escape from their
stressful lives"

30:44.844 --> 30:47.611
to hear you and Lisa
scream at each other?

30:47.646 --> 30:50.480
Are you [bleep]
kidding me?

30:50.516 --> 30:53.917
We don't always scream at each
other, but when we do--

30:53.953 --> 30:55.752
Look how small this place is.

30:55.788 --> 30:59.723
You live here, so you've got no
idea how many times you do it.

30:59.758 --> 31:01.892
The love, affection,

31:01.927 --> 31:05.095
and respect that they've shown
you is extraordinary.

31:05.130 --> 31:07.397
And the sad news is...

31:07.433 --> 31:09.633
you both don't deserve it.

31:09.668 --> 31:11.101
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

31:11.136 --> 31:13.036
(Jonathan)
I'm sorry.

31:13.072 --> 31:14.471
I will change.

31:14.506 --> 31:17.908
I just hope you guys
want to continue.

31:17.943 --> 31:21.912
I just want to say thank you
for your honesty,

31:21.947 --> 31:23.413
loyalty.

31:23.449 --> 31:24.815
There's some other
important people

31:24.850 --> 31:26.450
I want to introduce you to
this morning.

31:26.485 --> 31:27.684
Thank you.

31:27.720 --> 31:28.785
- Thank you.
- Thank you very much.

31:28.821 --> 31:30.621
[voice breaking]
Thank you, guys.

31:30.656 --> 31:37.761
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

31:37.796 --> 31:39.096
Good morning,
ladies and gentlemen.

31:39.131 --> 31:40.664
- Morning.
- Good morning.

31:40.699 --> 31:42.466
So, Lisa and Jonathan,

31:42.501 --> 31:45.335
I've asked
some ex-customers,

31:45.371 --> 31:49.673
locals, to come
and give you some feedback.

31:49.708 --> 31:51.408
Has anybody stayed there
recently?

31:51.443 --> 31:53.744
We did.
The room we stayed in--

31:53.779 --> 31:56.113
it had tools and screws...

31:56.148 --> 31:58.081
- and instruction manuals.
- Lightbulbs.

31:58.117 --> 31:59.716
Wow.

31:59.752 --> 32:01.485
So it's not just me.

32:01.520 --> 32:03.020
For the air conditioners
and stuff, yeah.

32:03.055 --> 32:04.888
That's right.
You're right.

32:04.924 --> 32:06.757
Madame, give us an insight
to your experience, please.

32:06.792 --> 32:09.960
I do have to say,
my husband ordered scallops,

32:09.995 --> 32:11.662
and they were raw.

32:11.697 --> 32:13.630
We returned them.

32:13.666 --> 32:16.500
The decor was very outdated,
and it feels very cluttered.

32:16.535 --> 32:18.402
You feel like you're locked
in a closet.

32:18.437 --> 32:19.836
It's just overwhelming

32:19.872 --> 32:21.605
when you're trying
to have a nice dinner.

32:21.640 --> 32:24.641
I would never come back there
if things don't change.

32:24.677 --> 32:26.209
Okay.

32:26.245 --> 32:27.878
What do you guys think
about the uniforms?

32:27.913 --> 32:29.079
It's a bit much.

32:29.114 --> 32:31.715
The poor ladies
were kind of revealing.

32:31.750 --> 32:34.685
Our server
was the nicest person,

32:34.720 --> 32:36.920
but I think it takes
a lot away from them.

32:36.956 --> 32:38.789
It doesn't need to be
in your face.

32:38.824 --> 32:41.792
The reputation locally
is crucial.

32:41.827 --> 32:43.460
What have you guys heard?

32:43.495 --> 32:46.463
I've heard that it's
a swingers' hangout.

32:46.498 --> 32:49.099
(woman)
I heard that as well.

32:49.134 --> 32:51.134
When I had mentioned
the Vienna, they say,

32:51.170 --> 32:53.704
"That's where
the swingers go."

32:53.739 --> 32:55.672
You eat downstairs,

32:55.708 --> 33:00.510
and then you go upstairs
is what I was told.

33:00.546 --> 33:02.746
But you've heard this before?

33:02.781 --> 33:05.849
- We've heard it for 13 years.
- I've heard it on the street.

33:05.884 --> 33:07.617
But is this due
to your late-night drinking

33:07.653 --> 33:09.453
- and the partying?
- I don't think so.

33:12.024 --> 33:15.192
But what I'm trying to say is
that there are no boundaries.

33:15.227 --> 33:16.593
It's an oasis down there

33:16.628 --> 33:19.629
that has got a Jacuzzi,
a massage table,

33:19.665 --> 33:24.134
and if the word has gotten out
around town and then--

33:24.169 --> 33:26.937
People misunderstood that room,
and that's where it all started.

33:26.972 --> 33:30.073
I'm just saying,
it's either a business,

33:30.109 --> 33:31.508
or it's your home.

33:31.543 --> 33:32.976
There's no crossover.

33:33.012 --> 33:35.178
The mixed messages
you're sending

33:35.214 --> 33:38.048
is your own fault
'cause you haven't been clear.

33:38.083 --> 33:40.517
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

33:40.552 --> 33:43.453
I used to come to the restaurant
probably every month or so,

33:43.489 --> 33:45.589
and I can tell

33:45.624 --> 33:48.225
you have a lot of, like,
passion for your heritage,

33:48.260 --> 33:51.094
but it's not
in the food anymore.

33:51.130 --> 33:55.599
If Gordon can help you
take your heritage and the food

33:55.634 --> 33:57.868
and modernize it
and you can progress with that,

33:57.903 --> 33:59.036
I'll come every Friday.

33:59.071 --> 34:01.104
Mark my words.
It's a promise.

34:01.140 --> 34:04.241
Do you have anything to say,
both of you, to these guests?

34:04.276 --> 34:06.910
Thank you so much
for your honesty and input

34:06.945 --> 34:08.245
and...

34:08.280 --> 34:10.047
really, really
appreciate it.

34:10.082 --> 34:12.983
We're gonna be making
some big changes

34:13.018 --> 34:16.553
to address many of the things
you talked about.

34:16.588 --> 34:19.990
The staff have been
incredibly loyal.

34:20.025 --> 34:21.258
They haven't been treated

34:21.293 --> 34:23.093
the way they
should have been treated.

34:23.128 --> 34:26.797
I'm undecided about these two,
but I am committed to that team,

34:26.832 --> 34:29.566
