36:55.847 --> 36:57.681
No lightbulb.
[chuckles]

36:57.716 --> 36:59.716
Oops.

36:59.751 --> 37:00.951
(Lisa)
Excuse me.

37:00.986 --> 37:02.085
(Gordon)
What's wrong?

37:02.120 --> 37:03.353
(Lisa)
No lightbulb in there.

37:03.388 --> 37:05.222
Don't worry about it.

37:05.257 --> 37:06.957
Who's complaining
about the lightbulb?

37:06.992 --> 37:09.125
Oh, just making sure
that they have enough light.

37:09.161 --> 37:11.027
Trying to turn it on,
then realized it later.

37:11.063 --> 37:12.896
Doesn't matter.
Doesn't matter.

37:12.931 --> 37:14.497
Let's focus on the big things.

37:14.533 --> 37:16.866
Are you always like this
over little details like that?

37:16.902 --> 37:19.836
I like to have things
feel right, and so...

37:19.871 --> 37:21.738
I'm feeling extra--
like, an extra need

37:21.773 --> 37:23.707
to make sure everything's
right--that's all.

37:23.742 --> 37:25.242
- OTT.
- Just a fusser.

37:25.277 --> 37:27.344
- OTT.
- Probably.

37:27.379 --> 37:29.412
- Whatever that means.
- Over the top.

37:29.448 --> 37:31.248
- [chuckles]
- Over the top.

37:31.283 --> 37:33.149
I guess I don't have to be
so over the top now, do I?

37:33.185 --> 37:34.884
You do not.

37:34.920 --> 37:37.087
[bleep].

37:41.793 --> 37:43.893
What is wrong
with her tonight?

37:43.929 --> 37:45.929
Do you think she's gonna go back
to her old ways when I leave?

37:45.964 --> 37:47.831
<i> (Melissa)</i>
<i> She might accidentally.</i>

37:47.866 --> 37:50.033
Customer's coming.
Welcome.

37:50.068 --> 37:52.369
<i> (Gordon)</i>
<i> While Lisa is nitpicking</i>
<i> everything unnecessarily...</i>

37:52.404 --> 37:55.005
(Jessica)
Do you guys have the appetizer
for table five?

37:55.040 --> 37:56.172
- Oh, sorry.
- We didn't give you that yet?

37:56.208 --> 37:57.474
No, you didn't.

37:57.509 --> 37:59.309
- No?
- No.

37:59.344 --> 38:01.244
<i> (Gordon)</i>
<i> Jonathan is lost</i>
<i> in the kitchen,</i>

38:01.280 --> 38:03.513
<i> and service is starting</i>
<i> to suffer.</i>

38:03.548 --> 38:05.248
What table number's this,
please?

38:05.284 --> 38:06.516
That is table number 11.

38:06.551 --> 38:07.984
They're waiting
on two flank steaks.

38:08.020 --> 38:09.886
Where's the flank steak?
Are they coming?

38:09.921 --> 38:12.289
Moments. Moments.
Minutes.

38:12.324 --> 38:14.024
Who's cooking the flank steak?

38:14.059 --> 38:16.426
Come on, guys, we can do one
four-top at the same time, yes?

38:16.461 --> 38:18.862
I designed the menu
around the size of the kitchen,

38:18.897 --> 38:21.064
the speed of both you
working together, okay?

38:21.099 --> 38:23.833
[bleep].
Flanks are going.

38:23.869 --> 38:25.502
Come back for the flank.

38:25.537 --> 38:27.003
What the hell is this?

38:27.039 --> 38:28.505
Look at me,
both of you, both of you.

38:28.540 --> 38:30.940
Cut the [bleep], okay?
Look at me.

38:30.976 --> 38:32.809
You're more than capable of
doing four [bleep] main courses

38:32.844 --> 38:34.010
at the same time,

38:34.046 --> 38:35.378
especially when
there's two of you.

38:35.414 --> 38:37.847
And one of those main courses
is the same dish.

38:37.883 --> 38:39.516
We got to talk to each other,
but I'm not gonna start sending

38:39.551 --> 38:41.251
one dish at a time
for a four-top.

38:41.286 --> 38:42.385
- Serious?
- Doesn't matter.

38:42.421 --> 38:45.889
It doesn't matter at all.

38:45.924 --> 38:47.524
Jonathan, hey, look at me.

38:47.559 --> 38:49.359
I need some [bleep] effort
from you a little bit.

38:49.394 --> 38:50.827
I need a little bit
of respect,

38:50.862 --> 38:52.062
a little bit of effort
from you, okay?

38:52.097 --> 38:53.496
Yeah, and look at me.

38:53.532 --> 38:55.198
You're the man holding
this [bleep] thing together.

38:55.233 --> 38:57.200
If you go down, the whole
[bleep] place is gonna go down.

38:57.235 --> 39:00.036
I need you to step up, okay?
I need you to talk a little bit.

39:00.072 --> 39:03.006
And I want four main courses
at the same [bleep] time.

39:03.041 --> 39:04.140
- Oh, dear God.

39:04.176 --> 39:05.208
- Jonathan.
- Yes?

39:05.243 --> 39:06.476
You can get your mind
set around

39:06.511 --> 39:12.315
four main courses
at the same [bleep] time.

39:12.351 --> 39:14.284
one table at a time,

39:14.319 --> 39:16.119
and we're gonna complete
that table,

39:16.154 --> 39:18.988
four main courses, three main
courses, five main courses.

39:19.024 --> 39:20.223
We're gonna talk together.

39:20.258 --> 39:21.658
Sausage goes with what--
the two soups?

39:21.693 --> 39:22.959
What's coming next?

39:22.994 --> 39:24.627
It's gonna be sausage,

39:24.663 --> 39:26.429
two carrot soups,
and a fried cheese.

39:26.465 --> 39:28.131
- Good.
- For table seven.

39:28.166 --> 39:29.299
Okay, so we're talking now.

39:29.334 --> 39:30.500
- Yep.
- Good.

39:30.535 --> 39:32.068
- Carrot?
- Thank you very much.

39:32.104 --> 39:33.636
I have your flank steaks.

39:33.672 --> 39:36.206
Your wine is coming
right away, okay?

39:36.241 --> 39:37.340
Your sausage.

39:37.376 --> 39:38.942
You guys
are all sharing, right?

39:38.977 --> 39:40.210
- Yes.
- Yeah.

39:40.245 --> 39:41.611
<i> (Jessica)</i>
<i> I think the new Vienna</i>

39:41.646 --> 39:43.680
<i> will definitely attract</i>
<i> a younger crowd.</i>

39:43.715 --> 39:46.583
- Oh, my God.
- So beautiful.

39:46.618 --> 39:48.485
<i> (Jessica)</i>
<i> I'm super excited</i>
<i> about the new changes,</i>

39:48.520 --> 39:50.520
and I hope they'll last.

39:50.555 --> 39:52.722
I really do.

39:52.758 --> 39:54.157
Right.

39:54.192 --> 39:55.625
We've had ups and downs,

39:55.660 --> 39:58.695
but tonight
is a prime example

39:58.730 --> 40:02.365
of how good and how profitable
this business can be.

40:02.401 --> 40:04.667
Customers loving the food.
They love the decor.

40:04.703 --> 40:07.003
I'm leaving you
with all the tools

40:07.038 --> 40:09.372
to get this place back
to where you want it to go.

40:09.408 --> 40:11.241
I do want to ask you
one thing.

40:11.276 --> 40:12.742
Sure.

40:12.778 --> 40:14.110
Is there anything
that's happened this week

40:14.146 --> 40:16.012
that you're not happy with?

40:16.047 --> 40:18.181
Yes, I had expected the Blumen's
room to be done, not the Koenig.

40:18.216 --> 40:20.216
It was the room
I didn't expect.

40:20.252 --> 40:23.019
And the room
that we've done...

40:23.054 --> 40:25.355
- Is amazing.
- Still has problems.

40:25.390 --> 40:27.457
Can I just tell you something
really important?

40:27.492 --> 40:29.492
- This is not a makeover show.
- I know that.

40:29.528 --> 40:31.227
- Yeah.
- But you're complaining about--

40:31.263 --> 40:33.029
I wasn't saying
I didn't love that room.

40:33.064 --> 40:35.064
